    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="678" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d678">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pera</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 15,
                                    1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Missionaries at Aintab, Bitlis, Harpoot, Marsovan, Cæsarea safe and
                            protected, but apprehensive. Ladies at Hadjin, I believe, safe. Porte
                            promises security for all missionaries. Have telegraphed that I would
                                <pb facs="0658" n="1392" xml:id="pg_1392"/> furnish ship to receive
                            if they desired to visit home. Gave no advice; they know dangers and
                            must decide. Mails and telegrams less impeded since my protest. Reliable
                            information from interior provinces shows destruction of many Armenian
                            villages, massacre of men, desecration and burning of monasteries and
                            churches, murdering of priests, enforced circumcising of boys, enforced
                            religious conversion of Armenian women as the price of life. It is
                            believed now that from 30,000 to 40,000 have been killed during the last
                            sixty days. I expect daily to hear that the army of some 3,000 at
                            Zeitoun and town are annihilated. They are surrounded.</p>
                <p>* * * * * * *</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
